**Smart Enumerations in DDD C# Application**

Smart enumerations are a way to implement enumerations in a more object-oriented and type-safe manner. They allow you to encapsulate the behavior and logic associated with each enumeration value within the enumeration class itself.

Here's an example of how to implement smart enumerations in a C# application using the `Enum` class and the `IEquatable<T>` interface.

**Enum Class**
```csharp
public abstract class EnumBase : IEquatable<EnumBase>
{
    protected EnumBase(string name, int value)
    {
        Name = name;
        Value = value;
    }

    public string Name { get; }
    public int Value { get; }

    public override bool Equals(object obj) => Equals(obj as EnumBase);
    public bool Equals(EnumBase other) => other != null && Name == other.Name && Value == other.Value;

    public override int GetHashCode() => HashCode.Combine(Name, Value);

    public static bool operator ==(EnumBase left, EnumBase right) => left.Equals(right);
    public static bool operator !=(EnumBase left, EnumBase right) => !left.Equals(right);
}
```

